overview: "The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep
  questionnaire application, providing a detailed specification and SOW. The
  assistant performed an initial code review and identified several missing
  features and areas for improvement. A detailed plan was then created and
  approved. In the current phase, the assistant has successfully implemented two
  high-priority items from the plan: a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness
  interference, which includes a safety warning for high-risk scores, and the
  detection and reporting of Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA). These
  changes involved updating data types, validation schemas, UI components for
  input, and the logic for generating both the web-based and PDF reports to
  accurately reflect these new assessments and provide relevant guidance."
